						<summary>

						<p>c. 13th Century.</p>						

						<p>This is a strange inscription recording the order of somebody (not specified) that no inscriptions should be engraved in the central shrine and in the <hi rend="italic">agra-maṇḍapa.</hi> It is warned that any transgressor would be considered as a traitor to the king, to god Śiva and to the community.</p>						

